0design%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df8dafb698ac0019dc5927%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bracket%20attaches%20to%20the%20window%20sill%2C%20while%20the%20open%20area%20allows%20you%20to%20still%20open%20the%20window%20while%20the%20AC%20is%20installed.%3Cp%3EMidea%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EWhile%20most%20air%20conditioners%20are%20a%20basic%20rectangular%20prism%2C%20the%20Midea%20U%20has%20a%20portion%20missing%20where%20the%20window%20would%20typically%20rest%20on%20top%20of%20the%20AC.%20Instead%2C%20your%20window%20can%20almost%20close%20in%20the%20U%20section%20between%20the%20two%20main%20bulky%20sections%20of%20the%20unit.%20This%20means%20you%20need%20less%20insulation%20to%20fill%20gaps%20left%20by%20the%20open%20window.%20It%20easily%20installs%20in%20single-hung%20or%20double-hung%20windows%20with%20a%20width%20of%2022%20to%2036%20inches%2C%20with%20a%20minimal%20height%20of%2013.75%20inches.%C2%A0%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20the%20window%20to%20keep%20it%20in%20place%20like%20most%20ACs%2C%20the%20Midea%20U%20comes%20with%20a%20support%20bracket%2C%20so%20you%20can%20open%20your%20window%20with%20the%20AC%20installed.%20The%20support%20bracket%20is%20a%20nice%20feature%20if%20you%20have%20a%20nagging%20fear%20of%20your%20AC%20falling%20out%20and%20squashing%20people%20down%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20design%20features%20make%20the%20Midea%20U%20a%20game%20changer.%20When%20the%20AC%20is%20installed%2C%20you%20can%20open%20your%20window%20all%20the%20way.%20This%20feature%20is%20great%20if%20you%20live%20where%20the%20temperature%20fluctuates%20drastically%20during%20AC%20season.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20you%20have%2090-degree%20days%20and%2060-degree%20nights%2C%20you%20can%20run%20the%20AC%20during%20the%20hottest%20part%20of%20the%20day.%20When%20the%20temp%20drops%2C%20turn%20off%20the%20AC%2C%20open%20the%